{
  "id": "jVMfGc-GJGY-GXyV4tDTX",
  "type": "BlogPost",
  "title": "Introducing alinea",
  "publishDate": "2022-09-13",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "id": "uTHitp5NX4kYClb964yjH",
      "index": "a0",
      "type": "TextBlock",
      "text": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "level": 1,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Introducing alinea"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For about 8 years we've been using a custom built CMS to power the websites, apps and services we build. Over time we've seen our development workflow move from PHP to JavaScript cloud deployments. As it was time for a fresh start to shake off some technical debt and achieve new goals we started work on a new content management system little over a year ago. Today an alpha version of alinea is available to the public."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "tdXnumJP39SF-2jM4tBZA",
          "type": "ImageBlock",
          "image": [
            {
              "id": "k_bd3GbePbhR16HT2nA5y",
              "index": "a0",
              "type": "entry",
              "entry": "xHdbCGvsMXq_4_EJvtyJ4"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "level": 2,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A quick intro"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Alinea is installable from NPM and bundles a few utilities to make it easy to manage and query content. A development server that boots the dashboard for you is included. This makes sure we're not tied to a specific web framework. The dashboard loads your configuration and lets you edit content based on a custom schema which can be composed of very rich set of fields - or added to by "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "building a custom field",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "attrs": {
                    "data-id": "v8gmN8mwB2IiH7cgZS4Ux",
                    "data-entry": "286iEJsjhd8R9NxN6EVg59fELyd",
                    "href": null,
                    "title": null
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " (which is little more than a React component)."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Content is structured hierarchically, following configuration settings to determine which page can have child pages. We've noticed that structuring content this way comes very natural for websites. Presenting the enduser with a tree of pages that follows the website's navigation makes the editing experience so transparent it requires zero training."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Published content changes persist on the file system in json format, allowing content to be version controlled with git. The dashboard can be hosted with a backend which authorises users, keeps drafts and pushes changes to Github."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "pviuHYPv4K_CQgbCRbEKx",
          "type": "ChapterLinkBlock",
          "link": [
            {
              "id": "JOpW2joyR1Q0NpA0FpEI7",
              "index": "a0",
              "type": "entry",
              "entry": "20580nQzbOBR3Lt4kIdxyRGglc6",
              "description": "Take it for a spin"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "level": 2,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "More features"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "level": 3,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Embedded database"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Content is indexed in an embedded SQLite database. The database is deployed with your code and can be queried during build time or at runtime with Node.js or inside an edge or serverless function. This will also enable us to provide full text search out of box without requiring an extra service."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "level": 3,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Fully typed"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Configuration and content is fully typed when making use of TypeScript. It's simply fantastic to see what impact configuration changes have on your codebase."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "level": 3,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Collaborative"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The editing experience is built on "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Y.js",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "link",
                  "attrs": {
                    "data-id": "vBGRn_VDaFKuQdMxrlbiy",
                    "data-entry": null,
                    "href": "https://docs.yjs.dev/",
                    "target": "_blank",
                    "title": null
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " primitives, which will allow multiple editors to collaborate without merge conflicts. We'll setup a WebRTC provider in the near future."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "level": 3,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Internationalization"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "textAlign": "left",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Content can be published in multiple languages and regions. We're polishing the UI that lets you switch and compare between languages."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
